---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Enrollment Forecasting System"
  description="Enrollment Forecasting System - AI-assisted development of ML-powered forecasting for educational enrollment planning."
>
    <section class="project-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="status-badge">Active Development</div>
            <h1 class="project-title">Enrollment Forecasting System</h1>
            <p class="project-lead">Using Claude Code to build a machine learning forecasting system that predicts student enrollments, enabling better resource planning and budgeting for educational institutions.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section--alt">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>The Challenge</h2>
            <p>Educational institutions need accurate enrollment forecasts to plan resources, hire faculty, and set budgets months in advance. With a high volume of annual leads and multiple intake periods, partners, programs, and marketing channels, manual forecasting was time-consuming, error-prone, and couldn't provide the granularity needed for effective planning.</p>
            <p class="mt-1">I used Claude Code to design a systematic approach that could replace hours of manual spreadsheet work with automated, data-driven predictions.</p>

            <h3 class="subsection-title--lg">The Goal</h3>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <p>Build a forecasting system that predicts enrollments for the next 3 intake periods across multiple dimensions: partner institutions, academic programs, and marketing channels.</p>
                <p><strong>Target accuracy:</strong> Within 5% margin of error, with confidence intervals for conservative/optimistic scenarios.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Development Approach</h2>
            <p>Rather than building a full production system immediately, I used Claude Code to design a phased approach that validates feasibility before major investment.</p>

            <h3 class="subsection-title mt-2">The Strategy</h3>
            <div class="card-grid">
                <div class="phase-card">
                    <h4>Pilot Phase</h4>
                    <div class="phase-card__subtitle">Proof-of-concept to validate approach</div>
                    <ul class="styled-list--sm">
                        <li>Limited scope (fewer dimensions)</li>
                        <li>Single Jupyter notebook</li>
                        <li>Manual weekly runs</li>
                        <li>Validate with stakeholders</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="phase-card__status"><strong>Status:</strong> Specification complete</div>
                </div>
                <div class="phase-card--active">
                    <h4>Production System ‚≠ê</h4>
                    <div class="phase-card__subtitle">Full-scale forecasting platform</div>
                    <ul class="styled-list--sm">
                        <li>All dimensions covered</li>
                        <li>Modular Python architecture</li>
                        <li>Semi-automated refresh</li>
                        <li>Power BI dashboard integration</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="phase-card__status"><strong>Status:</strong> Awaiting pilot validation</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section--alt">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>How It Works</h2>
            <p>Working with Claude Code, I designed a forecasting approach that combines historical patterns with current pipeline data.</p>

            <div class="content-box">
                <h4>Core Methodology</h4>
                <ol class="styled-list">
                    <li><strong>Analyze historical patterns:</strong> Look at how past leads converted over time</li>
                    <li><strong>Score current pipeline:</strong> Estimate conversion likelihood for leads already in the system</li>
                    <li><strong>Project future volume:</strong> Forecast how many new leads we'll receive</li>
                    <li><strong>Generate predictions:</strong> Combine all factors to predict enrollments with confidence ranges</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <h3 class="subsection-title--lg">Key Features</h3>
            <div class="card-grid--sm">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h4>Multi-Dimensional</h4>
                    <p>Forecasts broken down by partner institution, academic program, and marketing channel</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h4>Confidence Ranges</h4>
                    <p>Conservative, base, and optimistic scenarios for risk-aware planning</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h4>Data Quality Checks</h4>
                    <p>Automated validation with clear reporting of any issues</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h4>Dashboard Ready</h4>
                    <p>Outputs formatted for Power BI visualization and stakeholder reporting</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>My Role & Approach</h2>
            <p>This project demonstrates how domain knowledge combines with AI capabilities to design complex systems without traditional software engineering backgrounds.</p>

            <div class="mt-2">
                <h3 class="subsection-title">What I Brought:</h3>
                <ul class="styled-list">
                    <li>Understanding of enrollment cycles, lead behavior, and planning needs</li>
                    <li>Knowledge of data quality challenges</li>
                    <li>Business requirements for accuracy vs. runtime tradeoffs</li>
                    <li>Stakeholder communication and specification iteration</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-2">
                <h3 class="subsection-title">What Claude Code Brought:</h3>
                <ul class="styled-list">
                    <li>Statistical forecasting methodology and best practices</li>
                    <li>Python implementation guidance and code generation</li>
                    <li>Data pipeline architecture and validation design</li>
                    <li>Comprehensive technical documentation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="tech-stack-box">
                <h4>Technologies Used</h4>
                <div class="tech-badges">
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>Python</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>pandas</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>NumPy</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>XGBoost</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>Jupyter Notebooks</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>Power BI</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>Claude Code</span></span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section--alt">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Future Enhancements</h2>
            <p>Once the pilot validates the approach, planned enhancements include integrating machine learning for improved accuracy and full automation.</p>

            <div class="content-box">
                <h4>Phase 2 Roadmap</h4>
                <ul class="styled-list">
                    <li>XGBoost ML model integration for conversion prediction</li>
                    <li>Behavioral data enrichment (website activity, email engagement)</li>
                    <li>Azure automation for zero-touch weekly refresh</li>
                    <li>Advanced ensemble methods for &lt;15% margin of error</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</ProjectLayout>
